claim.claim-text:
1. A method of imaging a transparent media object, comprising:
passing light through a first scan line of the transparent media object;
focusing the light passed through the first scan line onto a first region of a photosensitive device, the first region extending along a transverse axis;
passing light through a second scan line of the transparent media object substantially concurrently with passage of the light passed through the first scan line; and
focusing the light passed through the second scan line onto a second region of the photosensitive device, the second region being offset alone the transverse axis from the first region.
